#backup database


su - oracle
rman target /
backup database
list backup

you can see the location of your datafile with:
su - oracle
rman target /
report schema

simulatingfailure:

#rename one of your datafile


1.have full and good backup
check it 
backup database

2.see your backup with:
su - oracle
rman target /
list backup

3.see the location of your datafile that you want to rename it with:

su - oracle
rman target /
report schema


4. first you nee to shutdown your db:
su - oracle
rman target /
shutdown immediate
exit

5.cd to location that you got from "report schema" in rman
then rename it:
mv /u01/dbfile/o12c/users01.dbf /u01/dbfile/o12c/users01.old
6.rman target /
startup:
ORA-01157: cannot identify/lock data file 4 - see DBWR trace file
ORA-01110: data file 4: '/u01/dbfile/o12c/users01.dbf'

solution:
rman target /
alter database mount;
restore database;
recover database;
alter database open;







